# ================================================================================
# FILE: .gitignore
# ================================================================================
#
# 🎓 FAANG-LEVEL LESSON: Git and .gitignore
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# WHAT IS .gitignore?
# ─────────────────────
# Git tracks changes to files. But SOME files should NEVER be tracked:
#   - .env files (contain secret API keys!)
#   - __pycache__ folders (Python bytecode, auto-generated)
#   - .db files (your local database — everyone has their own)
#   - node_modules (huge folders of dependencies)
#   - .DS_Store (Mac OS system files)
#   - Virtual environment folders (venv, .venv)
#
# .gitignore tells Git: "Ignore these files/folders completely."
#
# HOW GIT WORKS (Quick Overview):
# ─────────────────────────────────
# git init                     ← Start tracking this folder
# git add .                    ← Stage all changes
# git commit -m "message"      ← Save a snapshot
# git push origin main         ← Upload to GitHub
#
# RULE #1: NEVER commit .env files. API keys in version control = security breach.
# Real incident: Dev accidentally committed AWS key → $50,000 bill in 2 hours.
#
# TODO: Set up Git for this project:
#   1. git init (in project root)
#   2. git add .
#   3. git commit -m "Initial project structure"
#   4. Create repo on GitHub → git remote add origin URL → git push
# ================================================================================

# ── Python ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class
*.so
.Python

# ── Virtual Environments ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
venv/
.venv/
ENV/
env/
.env.local  # Keep .env.example but IGNORE the real .env
.env

# ── Database ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3

# ── Logs ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
logs/
*.log

# ── Exports & Generated Files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
exports/
backups/

# ── Test Cache ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.pytest_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/

# ── OS Files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store           # Mac
Thumbs.db           # Windows
desktop.ini         # Windows

# ── IDE Files ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp

# ── Large Asset Files (keep these out of Git — use cloud storage instead) ────
assets/frames/*.png
assets/frames/*.jpg
assets/processed/*.png
assets/processed/*.jpg
assets/scenes/**/*.mp4
assets/scenes/**/*.mov
assets/scenes/**/*.webm
